crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a backdoor Trojan. It daemonizes itself by forking and detaching from the terminal. It then establishes command-and-control (C2) communication with a hardcoded server, `levelframeblog.com`, using the path `/felix.php`. The C2 communication is encrypted with a custom scheme involving a hardcoded XOR key (`wLqfM]%wTx`~tUTbw>R^`) and Base64 encoding. The backdoor supports remote command execution via `popen`, file uploading, and file downloading, giving an attacker full control over the compromised machine.
